The South African government has indicated that British nationals wishing to leave the country will still be able to do so after 18 March.
On 20 March South African Airways announced it was suspending some international flights until 31 May. It is undergoing a business rescue process resulting in changes to its international and domestic flight schedules and some cancellations.
Check with your airline or tour operator promptly for further information regarding return flights to the UK.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
